summaries.short: Lorena's sentencing prompts Teresa to face the judge; the Colombian puts everything on the line.
summaries.full: Transsexual Antonia is sentenced to a male penitentiary. Lorena gets 30 years for homicide, prompting Teresa to confront the judge--and her own feelings. Meanwhile, Bambi arrives from the old prison, but her cheer turns to hatred as the Colombian is led away to Cristobal. Forced to stay at Capadocia, the Colombian decides to put it all on the line.

summaries.short: The Colombian's escape wreaks havoc; Teresa gets Lorena's case reopened, but fights with Santiago.
summaries.full: A kidnapping leads outlaw lovers to the prison. The Colombian's disappearance leaves Isabel furious and Bambi insane, and drives the escapee herself into a trap. Teresa convinces the judge to reopen Lorena's case, which upsets Santiago. Andrea appeals to Daniel, the Colombian turns to Bambi and Teresa agrees to help Antonia transfer to Capadocia.

summaries.short: Inmates old and new have tragic family stories to tell; a Mother's Day party ends abruptly.
summaries.full: The prison welcomes Marion, a virtuous nun caught carrying cocaine. Elsa, an inmate separated from her newborn son, goes deeper into depression. Magos tells Lorena her story of poisoning her small children to save them from a living hell. Outside, Teresa has her own family troubles. And the prison's Mother's Day party sees an astonishing end.

summaries.short: Bambi plans on Lorena's help in a drug operation; Teresa learns the identity of Santiago's past lover.
summaries.full: A powerful madam accused of white slavery arrives at the prison. Meanwhile, Bambi discovers Lorena's chemistry skills, which could help in a new drug operation. Teresa learns the identity of Santiago's past lover and tells Burian, who suffers a realization. Andrea loves Daniel, while he continues to falsely lure Teresa--ultimately into bed.

summaries.short: Santiago learns the truth about Teresa; Daniel spurns Andrea; Teresa resigns her position.
summaries.full: Guadalupe is a young mother imprisoned for a crime beyond her control. When Teresa confronts Santiago over his past with Isabel, the truth is revealed. Teresa shares her story with Lorena, as Isabel listens in. Daniel spurns Andrea, who hates Teresa for her participation. Antonia is savagely beaten during the night. Teresa resigns from Capadocia.
